<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF73CEA3FCD5FAB0DFD23A59" pageId="254" pageNumber="255" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF73CEA3FCD5FAB0DFD23A59" blockId="254.[810,1452,1377,1763]" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF73CEA3FCD5FAB0D8F73955" bold="true" box="[810,932,1377,1403]" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF73CEA3FBC7FAB0DFA13955" box="[1080,1266,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">A. uruguayense</emphasis>
(Ríos-Tamayo, 2019, fig. 8 I–J) resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF73CEA3FB2BFA54DEF839B1" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1923" box="[1236,1451,1413,1439]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="254" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubiomaculatus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF73CEA3FB2BFA54DEF839B1" box="[1236,1451,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">A. dubiomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by shape of the palpal bulb but can be distinguished by uniform leg article coloration. Females are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF73CEA3FC70FA20DF743A25" box="[911,1063,1521,1547]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="254" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraitinga">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF73CEA3FC70FA20DF743A25" box="[911,1063,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">A. paraitinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of the spermathecal lateral swellings and external lobes (
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF73CEA3FB40F9C4DE783A01" box="[1215,1323,1557,1584]" captionStart="FIGURE 59" captionStartId="66.[136,235,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,192,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-193@66.[151,1436,189,1497]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 59. Actinopus paraitinga sp. nov., male: A–C IBSP 113424: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D MNRJ 1: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale line: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597361" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597361/files/figure.png" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">Fig. 59 D</figureCitation>
) but can be recognized by the larger, more pronounced internal lobes (Ríos-Tamayo, 2019, fig. 9 E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
